cs.PL, cs.LO, cs.SE, cs.AR, cs.CR 

This paper deals with the verification of compiler optimizations, which is a topic closely related to programming languages (cs.PL) and logic (cs.LO). The paper also discusses the challenges of verifying optimizations on an axiomatic relaxed model, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). Additionally, the paper deals with memory models, which is a topic related to computer architecture (cs.AR) and cryptography (cs.CR).
